ourselves into the fact

00:41:14.330 --> 00:41:16.520 align:middle line:84%
that there have been
five major extinctions,

00:41:16.520 --> 00:41:20.510 align:middle line:84%
that there have been extinction
events where 90% of the beings

00:41:20.510 --> 00:41:22.610 align:middle line:90%
just were erased--

00:41:22.610 --> 00:41:25.970 align:middle line:84%
and then, in fact, we are
the product of the space left

00:41:25.970 --> 00:41:30.860 align:middle line:84%
behind by extinction events
but then the open space for new

00:41:30.860 --> 00:41:35.120 align:middle line:84%
experimentations and
morphology and that we can't--

00:41:35.120 --> 00:41:37.130 align:middle line:84%
when we weave ourselves
into that deep time,

00:41:37.130 --> 00:41:41.720 align:middle line:90%
it's an embrace that is--

00:41:41.720 --> 00:41:43.520 align:middle line:90%
it's geological.

00:41:43.520 --> 00:41:44.600 align:middle line:90%
It's microbial.

00:41:44.600 --> 00:41:48.050 align:middle line:84%
It's not just one human
embracing another human.

00:41:48.050 --> 00:41:49.880 align:middle line:90%
And that's what comforts me.

00:41:49.880 --> 00:41:53.210 align:middle line:84%
It's just seeing that there's
a story going on that's so much

00:41:53.210 --> 00:41:54.995 align:middle line:90%
longer than my lifetime.

00:41:54.995 --> 00:41:56.470 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Playing the long game.

00:41:56.470 --> 00:41:57.270 align:middle line:90%
>>STRAND: Yeah.

00:41:57.270 --> 00:41:58.145 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:41:58.145 --> 00:42:01.140 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And I love
